Installation Instructions
*************************

To install HPX with an MPI bootstrapper and Photon as the network layer, follow these steps:

1.  Install MPI
2.  Install Photon
3.  Run ./bootstrap in the HPX source directory
4.  Set the environment variable PHOTON_CFLAGS=-I/path/to/photon/include
5.  Set the environment variable PHOTON_LIBS=-L/path/to/photon/lib
6.  Set the environment variable MPI_CFLAGS=-I/path/to/mpi/include
7.  Set the environment variable MPI_LIBS=-L/path/to/mpi/lib -lmpi
8.  In the HPX source directory, run ./configure --prefix=/path/to/hpx --with-photon --with-mpi

This means using a Bash shell under Linux, you would type:

export PHOTON_CFLAGS=-I/usr/photon/include
export PHOTON_LIBS=-L/usr/photon/lib
export MPI_CFLAGS=-I/usr/mpi/include
export MPI_LIBS=-L/usr/mpi/lib -lmpi
./bootstrap
./configure --prefix=/usr/hpx --with-photon --with-mpi
make
make install

